    <h2>Digital Sovereignty & The Fediverse</h2>
    <p>
      The fediverse represents a new approach to social networking—one that's decentralized, community-owned, and built on open protocols. Unlike mainstream platforms controlled by corporations, fediverse networks (like Mastodon, PeerTube, and Pixelfed) are interconnected yet independently operated.
    </p>
    <p>
      This means greater digital sovereignty: the ability to control your online presence, data, and connections without being subject to algorithmic manipulation or surveillance capitalism. For organizations and communities, the fediverse offers a way to engage authentically, build genuine connections, and align your digital presence with your values.
    </p>
    <a href="/fediverse" class="dt_a11y-btn button">Explore the Fediverse</a>
  </div>
</section>

