    <h2>Fediverse and IndieWeb</h2>
    <p>
      The IndieWeb movement champions web ownership—creating and maintaining your own website as your primary online identity. It's about taking back control from platforms that monetize your content and attention.
    </p>
    <p>
      By combining IndieWeb principles with fediverse connections, you can create a powerful, independent digital presence that still enables social interaction. Your content lives on your own domain, but can be shared and discussed across the decentralized social web. This approach gives you the best of both worlds: ownership and community.
    </p>
